{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"6fe7effe-279c-47b8-ad1c-c0a43cc35684","content":"The directory is empty, so this is a general guidance question. Here's how to migrate:\n\n**Replace `VSTest@3` with `DotNetCoreCLI@2` (or a plain `script` step) using `dotnet test`.**\n\nMicrosoft.Testing.Platform is invoked via `dotnet test`, not `vstest.console`. Key changes:\n\n```yaml\n# BEFORE (VSTest@3)\n- task: VSTest@3\n  inputs:\n    testAssemblies: '**/*Tests.dll'\n    resultsFolder: $(Agent.TempDirectory)/TestResults\n    codeCoverageEnabled: true\n\n# AFTER (dotnet test with Microsoft.Testing.Platform)\n- task: DotNetCoreCLI@2\n  displayName: 'Run Tests'\n  inputs:\n    command: test\n    projects: '**/*Tests.csproj'\n    arguments: >\n      --logger \"trx;LogFileName=results.trx\"\n      --results-directory $(Agent.TempDirectory)/TestResults\n      --collect \"Code Coverage\"\n```\n\n**What else to do:**\n\n1. **NuGet packages** — in each test project, add:\n   ```xml\n   <PackageReference Include=\"Microsoft.Testing.Platform\" Version=\"1.*\" />\n   <PackageReference Include=\"MSTest.TestFramework\" Version=\"3.*\" />\n   <PackageReference Include=\"MSTest.TestAdapter\" Version=\"3.*\" />\n   ```\n   Or use the newer unified `MSTest` meta-package (v3+), and enable the platform in your `.csproj`:\n   ```xml\n   <EnableMSTestRunner>true</EnableMSTestRunner>\n   <OutputType>Exe</OutputType>\n   ```\n\n2. **Publish TRX results** — add a step after the test step:\n   ```yaml\n   - task: PublishTestResults@2\n     condition: always()\n     inputs:\n       testResultsFormat: VSTest\n       testResultsFiles: '$(Agent.TempDirectory)/TestResults/**/*.trx'\n   ```\n\n3. **Publish code coverage** — add:\n   ```yaml\n   - task: PublishCodeCoverageResults@2\n     condition: always()\n     inputs:\n       summaryFileLocation: '$(Agent.TempDirectory)/TestResults/**/*.cobertura.xml'\n   ```\n   For Cobertura format, use `--collect \"XPlat Code Coverage\"` instead.\n\n**Key differences from VSTest@3:**\n- Tests are discovered by **project** (`.csproj`), not by compiled assembly (`.dll`)\n- No more `vstest.console.exe` — the test platform is hosted in-process\n- TRX logging and coverage collection are explicit CLI arguments","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"e72b1d34-7201-46e7-8c54-4366a03a8cba","outputTokens":650,"requestId":"CFE0:1FFE72:62A0C71:6DCD752:69EC0EA7"},"id":"25b5f67f-81af-4548-9f64-19ee1e2f4c30","timestamp":"2026-04-25T00:45:40.043Z","parentId":"df1136c0-1fd9-4988-b3e0-d10ba438057a"}
